resence of {\\it multiple} light cone-like structures which persists\neven when $\\alpha$ is large. We also show that the nature of space-time\ndependence of the mutual information of long-ranged Hamiltonians with $\\alpha\n\\le 2$ differs qualitatively from their short-ranged counterparts with $\\alpha\n> 2$ for any drive frequency and relate this difference to the behavior of the\nFloquet group velocity of such driven system.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 26 Sep 2017 09:04:14 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 31 Oct 2017 00:53:30 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-07-13"}
